  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-16045">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      <b>Preventing Impaired Driving.</b> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16045 mb-requirement-id-16046">
        (a) Explain why a distracted driver must not operate a motor vehicle.
        List five common distractions, explain how driver distractions
        contribute to traffic accidents, and tell how drivers can minimize
        distractions. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/zWdfeE2YsNc" target="_blank"
          >Distracted Driving (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16045 mb-requirement-id-16047">
        (b) Explain why a driver impaired by alcohol, drugs, or other substances
        must not operate a motor vehicle. Describe how alcohol, cold
        medications, and prescription and illegal drugs affect driving
        abilities. For the state where you live, find out what is the legal
        blood alcohol concentration and what are the consequences for driving
        while intoxicated or driving under the influence. Find out what the
        open-container law is in your state. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/6uH75bY8Gd0" target="_blank"
          >The Deadly Truth About Drinking and Driving (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/1cs2t3SiSNw" target="_blank"
          >Blood Alcohol Content &amp; Driving: What You Need to Know (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16045 mb-requirement-id-16048">
        (c) Explain why a fatigued driver must not operate a motor vehicle.
        Describe how drivers must plan to be alert for safely transporting
        families, friends, Scouts, and themselves. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/YhK2VLGYMng?si=YdLr0d7mJ020XzSV"
          target="_blank"
          >Recognizing Fatigue—Warning Signs (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/fVl88Q5DJ2w" target="_blank"
          >Driver Tiredness, Fatigue, and Road Safety (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16045 mb-requirement-id-16049">
        (d) Describe mistakes that new drivers make, how those mistakes increase
        their risk of collisions, how drivers can reduce this risk, and how
        driving behavior affects automobile insurance rates. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://studentdrivercarmagnets.com/blogs/news/common-driving-mistakes"
          target="_blank"
          >7 Common Mistakes New Drivers Make—and How to Avoid Them (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Arrgxna3L2E" target="_blank"
          >Most Common Driving Mistakes to Avoid (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-16050">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      <b>Vehicle Safety.</b> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16050 mb-requirement-id-16051">
        (a) Demonstrate how to wear a lap and shoulder belt properly. Explain
        why it is important for the driver and all passengers, including
        children sitting in age-appropriate seats, to always wear their seat
        belts. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Cq1auN7xtlo" target="_blank"
          >How to Wear a Seat Belt Properly (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/TPGjlzUenL0" target="_blank"
          >Car Seat Safety (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16050 mb-requirement-id-16052">
        (b) List five safety features found in motor vehicles besides occupant
        restraint systems. Describe each safety feature, how each works, and how
        each contributes to safety. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/D2kM8gEoGYY" target="_blank"
          >10 Car Safety Features That Every Car Must Have (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-16053">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      <b>Auto Maintenance and Safety Checkups.</b> With adult supervision and
      using a vehicle that you have access to, do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16053 mb-requirement-id-16054">
        (a) Demonstrate that all driving lights and signaling lights are clear
        and operational. Show where the switches are for these lights. Explain
        how drivers use lights to drive safely and courteously and to
        communicate with other drivers. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/8FW-7dfAIwQ" target="_blank"
          >Types of Car Lights &amp; Their Purposes (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16053 mb-requirement-id-16055">
        (b) Explain issues that might affect the driver's ability to see through
        the front, rear, and side windows. Demonstrate with a smear-and-clear
        test if the windshield wiper blades will clear the windshield completely
        or need to be replaced. Describe instances in good and bad weather when
        windshield wipers are important to safe driving. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/MmA6Cbn5vH8" target="_blank"
          >How to Check Your Wipers (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16053 mb-requirement-id-16056">
        (c) Demonstrate how to find the vehicle's recommended tire pressures,
        how to check tire pressures, and how to check for adequate tire tread
        depth. Explain why proper tire pressure and tread depth are important to
        traction, stopping distances, tire wear, and fuel economy. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/2Tcvmp4Cqao" target="_blank"
          >How to Check Your Tires (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16053 mb-requirement-id-16057">
        (d) Check the vehicle for tools needed to change a flat tire or to use
        tire sealant to fix a puncture. Demonstrate you know how to change a
        flat tire and how to use tire sealant. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/X3kjWwCENX4" target="_blank"
          >Tire Inflator and Sealant Kit (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16053 mb-requirement-id-16067">
        (e) In a location away from traffic hazards, mark off the reaction
        distances and braking distances that a car will travel as it makes an
        emergency stop at 25, 55, and 70 miles per hour on level dry and level
        wet pavement. Discuss how these distances change for normal and impaired
        drivers, for day and night driving, and for weather conditions.
        <br /><br /><b>Note: </b>Use the graphics template in the
        <i>Traffic Safety</i> merit badge pamphlet or one approved by your
        counselor to set up this demonstration. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Requirement%20Resources/Traffic%20Safety/Stopping%20Distances%20Table%20and%20Graphs.pdf?_t=1764661254"
          target="_blank"
          >Stopping Distance Table and Graphs (PDF)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/ZLHgYgEAPhY" target="_blank"
          >Thinking, Braking, and Stopping Distances (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/3mDp0k8Nfjc?si=Zoy8bAbLADxtlsz3"
          target="_blank"
          >Stopping Distance Demonstration (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-16058">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      <b>Traffic Safety and the Law.</b> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16058 mb-requirement-id-16059">
        (a) Describe at least three examples of traffic laws that apply to
        drivers of motor vehicles and to bicyclists. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/TAwv_BPBAnc" target="_blank"
          >Bicycle Rules of the Road (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16058 mb-requirement-id-16060">
        (b) Explain procedures and etiquette a driver should follow if a law
        enforcement officer stops their vehicle. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/twTVubwyp4E?si=asTzoxN88uwMYZ1T"
          target="_blank"
          >Traffic Stop Etiquette (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16058 mb-requirement-id-16061">
        (c) Explain procedures that drivers should follow if they are involved
        in a car accident. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/ljjGN6xST_A?si=P4u_Sc1h6nF6rsnL"
          target="_blank"
          >What to Do After a Car Accident (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16058 mb-requirement-id-16062">
        (d) Name the three documents that drivers are required by law to carry
        whenever they operate a motor vehicle. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.thirdcoastautos.com/blog/what-paperwork-should-you-keep-in-your-car"
          target="_blank"
          >Three Documents You Should Always Have in Your Car (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-16063">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      <b>Road Designs and Signs.</b> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16063 mb-requirement-id-16064">
        (a) Explain how road designs for intersections, medians, and road
        shoulders contribute to traffic safety. Discuss safety features of
        interstate highways. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/SdYilULmeAc" target="_blank"
          >How Highways Are Designed and Built (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16063 mb-requirement-id-16065">
        (b) Explain how color and shape help drivers recognize and understand
        the information presented on traffic and roadway signs. Explain the
        purpose of different types of signs, signals, and pavement markings.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/KxrfkcDAgsY" target="_blank"
          >Understanding Road Signs (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Hj87mH_a4jk" target="_blank"
          >Traffic Signals (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Lq3p5i9g9c0" target="_blank"
          >Pavement Markings (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-16068">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      <b>Sharing the Road.</b> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16068 mb-requirement-id-16069">
        (a) Describe the difference in nighttime visibility between a properly
        lit bicycle and rider (or a pedestrian) wearing reflective material and
        a bicycle and rider with no lights (or a pedestrian) dressed in dark
        clothing without reflective material. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/zm_uXZJnCSk" target="_blank"
          >Bike Safety - Sharing the Road (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/DJc18FiARLc?si=tV7T0fXYYDHGVdmm"
          target="_blank"
          >The Basics of Bicycle Safety (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/uYhwXwVDlF0?si=3M13qEkL7YbemovD"
          target="_blank"
          >What to Do to Make Driving at Night Safer (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16068 mb-requirement-id-16070">
        (b) Name at least four safety measures that pedestrians, including
        hikers, should follow as they walk along or across streets or roadways.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/Lsv1TSy8JbA?si=Yv-ODDQIlOvnSNbC"
          target="_blank"
          >The Basics of Pedestrian Safety (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16068 mb-requirement-id-16071">
        (c) Name at least four safety measures that drivers of motor vehicles
        should follow if they approach a school bus making its stops at pick-up
        and drop-off locations. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/XSYE2z3LCUI" target="_blank"
          >Driving Safety 101: School Bus Safety (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16068 mb-requirement-id-16072">
        (d) Discuss the risks associated with blind spots on cars and trucks and
        how drivers can prevent lane change crashes. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/bkX_NSCM0Hw" target="_blank"
          >Blind Spots Lessons (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/H0EA2RD-w2c" target="_blank"
          >Lane Changes (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-16073">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      <b>Traffic, Your Community, and You.</b> Do ONE of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16073 mb-requirement-id-16074">
        (a) Interview a traffic law enforcement officer or a traffic safety
        professional in your community to identify what three traffic safety
        problems the officer is most concerned about. Discuss with your
        counselor possible ways to solve one of those problems. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/l39mAUI868w?si=zf_CZPPFbjbUstOW"
          target="_blank"
          >Engineering and Inspector Careers (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/5UQaWsVS4Ww?si=-wXVuWGizEMaz7dZ"
          target="_blank"
          >Women in Road Safety Careers (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16073 mb-requirement-id-16075">
        (b) Write a personal traffic safety pledge, addressing three of your
        most concerning issues relating to traffic safety. Discuss your pledge
        with your counselor. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://www.t-driver.com/pledge/" target="_blank"
          >Take the Pledge (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.healthychildren.org/English/ages-stages/teen/safety/Pages/teen-driving-agreement.aspx"
          target="_blank"
          >Parent-Teen Driving Agreement (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-16073 mb-requirement-id-16076">
        (c) Initiate and organize an activity or event to demonstrate the
        importance of traffic safety. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/v8zcyY194jI?si=St3aTOW9HnAHT7oh"
          target="_blank"
          >Teen Driving Safety Event (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-16077">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 8. </span>
      <b>Careers.</b> Explore careers related to traffic safety. Research one
      career to learn about the training and education needed, costs, job
      prospects, salary, job duties, and career advancement. Your research
      methods may include—with your parent or guardian's permission—an internet
      or library search, an interview with a professional in the field, or a
      visit to a location where people in this career work. Discuss with your
      counselor both your findings and what about this profession might make it
      an interesting career. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/RA5GljWCPhQ?si=tzgUiIj2PWhx2-j3" target="_blank"
        >What It's Like to Work in Traffic Control and Safety in Road
        Construction (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/qcLQd4eTj8A?si=aQ2EYV2mPDoWlf1Q" target="_blank"
        >On The Job: Traffic Signal Technician (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
